			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Zombie Studios Consumer Games Division is currently looking for a Producer will be responsible for managing all aspects of the production of individual games and games-related interactive projects for virtual worlds, websites, online and other mobile initiatives and applications. Responsibilities include managing games production team, the timeline, budget, scope, client interaction and updates, scheduling milestones, budget planning and accountability as well as maintaining day-to-day relationships with in-house development team and external customers.<br />
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage the development of individual games and games-related interactive applications including virtual worlds, websites, online and mobile initiatives, from pre-production to final product release, to meet defined budgets, schedules and quality benchmarks.</li>
<li>
The ability to communicate a strong creative approach to the games is imperative.</li>
<li>
Responsible for the timely delivery of the projects.</li>
<li>
Create and manage schedule to ensure that everyone is clear on all deliverables &ndash; internal and external.</li>
<li>
Continuously assess risk and keep scope of the project in line with budget and schedule with keen attention to quality.</li>
<li>
Directly manage and maintain close communication with team leads and production personnel and provide team members with material and technical support as needed.</li>
<li>
Ensure that each member of the team is working from a tracked schedule and has a strong sense of ownership, responsibility and accountability for the quality and timeliness of their contribution.</li>
<li>
Identify and resolve conflicts between schedule, budget and design goals.</li>
<li>
Foster positive working relationships, teamwork and communication within the development team.</li>
<li>
Identify, communicate, and direct key product features/qualities that will drive product success.</li>
<li>
Manage external developers and contractors to contractual requirements.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
3-5 years&rsquo; experience in online and/or games and mobile development.</li>
<li>
Budget and financial management experience a plus.</li>
<li>
Successful track record in the development of high profile entertainment software products.</li>
<li>
Strong interactive knowledge across a variety of platforms and genres.</li>
<li>
Must have strong verbal, written and communication skills.</li>
<li>
Proficiency with Windows, Office- including Excel, Word and PowerPoint, scheduling software and bug-tracking software (Jira/Greenhopper/Confluence a big plus).</li>
<li>
Strong sense of task ownership and responsibility.</li>
<li>
Highly organized, enthusiastic and motivated.</li>
<li>
Ability to work collaboratively absolutely required.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
